      • bySameCity

        public static List<BSIPData> bySameCity(BSIPData source)
        As described in method header; finds the other non-same IPData records that geolocate to the same country/region/city pairing.
        Parameters:
        source - The IPData to use to seed the search
        Returns:
        A list of IPDatas in the same region, or nothing if none found.

      • byExactIP

        ip - The BSIP record to use for IPData retrieval
        Returns:
        the matching BSIPData or null if no match

      • byContainsIP

        public static BSIPData byContainsIP(BSIP ip)
        Finds the first subnet that fully contains the given BSIP's IP/CIDR, if any.
        Parameters:
        ip - The BSIP record to base the lookup on
        Returns:
        The BSIPData record that contains the IP/CIDR, or null if none found.

        Returns:
        a list; empty if nothing found.

      • create

        public static BSIPData create(BSIP ip,
                              String continent,
                              String country,
                              String region,
                              String city,
                              String postal,
                              Double lat,
                              Double lon,
                              String domain,
                              String provider,
                              String registeredAs,
                              String _connection,
                              float proxy,
                              String source,
                              String comment)
        This does NOT check for prior existence. Must be managed elsewhere.
        Parameters:
        ip - The BSIP record to bind to. Must not be null.
        continent - The continent where this IP is registered to
        country - The country where this IP is registered to
        region - The region where this IP is registered to
        city - The city where this IP is registered to
        postal - The postal / zip code where this IP is registered to
        lat - The latitude
        lon - The longitude
        domain - The domain that maps to this IP / range
        provider - The provider for this IP / range
        registeredAs - Any registration information for this IP / range
        _connection - The connection source for this IP / range
        proxy - The likelihood this is a proxy -- higher number for more likelihood. Assumes 0 - no, 3 - likely, 4 - definite
        source - The source of this record (Cloud9? Tor? IP-API?)
        comment - Any comments recorded against the BSIPData.
        Returns:
        The new BSIPData if successful

        public void flush()

      • saveDirty

        public static void saveDirty()
        Pulls from the dirty queue and commits updates to the backing DB in batches. Allows for high volume changes w/o swamping the DB with churn. Note that inserts are direct, to ensure IDs and relationship consistency is upheld

      • preload

        public static long preload(long offset,
                           int limit)
        Triggers a segmented preload of valid BSIPData segments. Items marked invalid are not loaded. Fills the cache with entries.
        Parameters:
        offset - Starting point
        limit - How many to load
        Returns:
        The largest ID encountered during this load, or -1 if nothing loaded.
